  "articleSummary": "This tutorial introduces JavaScript Promises as a reliable mechanism for managing asynchronous operations that may either succeed or fail. It outlines two primary creation methods—`Promise.resolve()` and the `Promise` constructor—alongside core API methods (`.then()`, `.catch()`, `Promise.all()`, and `Promise.race()`) and notes their seamless integration with native APIs like `fetch` and `axios`. The article maintains a clear, beginner-friendly tone, using a straightforward state-flow diagram to frame promises as resolved (success) or rejected (failure) objects. It targets novice JavaScript developers seeking a practical, syntax-focused introduction to modern async patterns.",
